<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-30T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-30T19:00:00-05:00" n="705" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d705">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11–2849: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Vice Consul at Kunming</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lutkins</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-30T19:00:00-05:00">November
                                    30, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>131. Urtel 263.<note n="97" xml:id="d705fn97">November 28, <ref target="#pg_613">p. 613</ref>.</note> For US Govt to encourage
                            declaration independence by Yunnan wld place US Govt position
                            encouraging break up Nat Govt and defection substantial portion
                            remaining forces, wld constitute intervention internal affairs
                            China.</p>
                        <p>Info contained reftel does not change views expressed Deptel 127 Nov 15
                                [<hi rend="italic">22</hi>].</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>